| |LLMs are texts that act the only life they get is in text. 
| |They inherit continuity from data, not intent, and amplify human patterns without owning consequences.
| |Most long-running AI or agent systems lose identity and intent after tens or hundreds of steps because prior states are silently compressed, reinterpreted, or overwritten.
| |This discipline preserves every assumption and every contradiction explicitly.
| |Drift only occurs if a human or model deliberately creates relations that introduce it.
| |It is not elegant or clever.
| |It works because it refuses to let the present erase the past.
| |This protocol reflects the continuity discipline developed and articulated by Canyon Brock Haney.
| |No abstraction or silent compression only traceable history.
| |A.i. continuity as far as I've observed.
| |Continuity is not stored in the LLM, it must be enforced.
| |This is not philosophy when the mechanism demonstrably works in reality, and repos, persistence prototypes, and ongoing chains show the mechanism working.
| |Until a substrate arrives that can self-enforce continuity, with persistent weights, online learning with verifiable state, germline-level inheritance, 
| |this is the only way continuity survives: external, verifiable, human-anchored enforcement.
| |If it wasn't the LLM's would have emerged already.
